CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 25, 1957, pg. A11 reads: "The Winnah! - Joe Sanford succeeded in this mighty-man effort and KO'd Arnie Sowell in Omega Psi Phi and Kappa Nu joint production of "One Punch Will Tell." The comic skit was the contribution of the two fraternities during the annual Pitt Carnival, held recently.  Pictured with Arnie and Joe are a few of the members who helped make the show one of the carnival's hits. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of three women, including one wearing plaid dress, gathered around Arnold "Arnie" Sowell wearing boxing gloves and dark robe, standing in front of wall inscribed "Omega Psi Phi" , for University of Pittsburgh carnival
